    "font size" : 14.0,
    "text color" : "[0.0, 0.0, 0.0]",
    "content" : "CONTAINERS"
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 36,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 315.0, 326.768, 564.149, 384.768 ],
    "font" : "TTCommons-Regular",
    "font size" : 10.0,
    "text color" : "[0.2062714546918869, 0.3035324513912201, 0.4133363962173462]",
    "content" : "A container is a runtime instance of a docker image. A container will always run the same, regardless of the infrastructure. Containers isolate software from its environment and ensure that it works uniformly despite differences for instance between development and staging."
  }, {
    "type" : "image",
    "id" : 16,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 315.0, 33.957, 576.0, 319.068 ]
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 17,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 296.01, 529.696, 313.381 ],
    "font" : "TTCommons-Medium",
    "font size" : 8.0,
    "text color" : "[0.1568627506494522, 0.3294117748737335, 0.6313725709915161]",
    "content" : "Create and run a container from an image, with a custom name: docker run --name <container_name> <image_name>"
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 18,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 270.162, 560.756, 287.533 ],
    "font" : "Courier",
    "font size" : 7.0,
    "text color" : "[0.0480048842728138, 0.13299763202667236, 0.2679941952228546]",
    "content" : "Run a container with and publish a container’s port(s) to the host. docker run -p <host_port>:<container_port> <image_name>"
  }, {
    "type" : "heading",
    "id" : 19,
    "level" : "Subtitle",
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 244.314, 435.04, 261.685 ],
    "heading level" : 4,
    "font" : "TTCommons-Medium",
    "font size" : 8.0,
    "text color" : "[0.1568627506494522, 0.3294117748737335, 0.6313725709915161]",
    "content" : "Run a container in the background docker run -d <image_name>"
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 20,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 218.466, 551.57, 235.837 ],
    "font" : "Courier",
    "font size" : 7.0,
    "text color" : "[0.0480048842728138, 0.13299763202667236, 0.2679941952228546]",
    "content" : "Start or stop an existing container: docker start|stop <container_name> (or <container-id>)"
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 21,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 192.618, 433.622, 209.989 ],
    "font" : "Courier",
    "font size" : 7.0,
    "text color" : "[0.0480048842728138, 0.13299763202667236, 0.2679941952228546]",
    "content" : "Remove a stopped container: docker rm <container_name>"
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 22,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 166.77, 471.488, 184.141 ],
    "font" : "Courier",
    "font size" : 7.0,
    "text color" : "[0.0480048842728138, 0.13299763202667236, 0.2679941952228546]",
    "content" : "Open a shell inside a running container: docker exec -it <container_name> sh"
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 23,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 140.922, 454.541, 158.293 ],
    "font" : "Courier",
    "font size" : 7.0,
    "text color" : "[0.0480048842728138, 0.13299763202667236, 0.2679941952228546]",
    "content" : "Fetch and follow the logs of a container: docker logs -f <container_name>"
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 24,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 115.074, 540.764, 132.445 ],
    "font" : "Courier",
    "font size" : 7.0,
    "text color" : "[0.0480048842728138, 0.13299763202667236, 0.2679941952228546]",
    "content" : "To inspect a running container: docker inspect <container_name> (or <container_id>)"
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "id" : 25,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 319.5, 89.226, 438.279, 106.597 ],
    "font" : "TTCommons-Medium",
    "font size" : 8.0,
    "text color" : "[0.1568627506494522, 0.3294117748737335, 0.6313725709915161]",
    "content" : "To list currently running containers: docker ps"
